00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:27.117
this right over here is standard form

00:00:27.117 --> 00:00:31.367
and I want to convert it
to slope-intercept form,

00:00:34.517 --> 00:00:38.987
which has the form of y is
equal to the slope times x

00:00:38.987 --> 00:00:43.957
plus the y-coordinate of the y-intercept.

00:00:43.957 --> 00:00:45.917
So let's see how we do this.

00:00:45.917 --> 00:00:48.187
It's just gonna take a little
bit of algebraic manipulation

00:00:48.187 --> 00:00:50.717
and, like always, I encourage
you to pause the video

00:00:50.717 --> 00:00:53.657
and try to work through it
on your own before I do it.

00:00:53.657 --> 00:00:54.957
So what we really wanna do is we just

00:00:54.957 --> 00:00:57.817
wanna isolate the y here
on the left hand side

00:00:57.817 --> 00:01:00.757
so I wanna get rid of
this negative seven x

00:01:00.757 --> 00:01:03.317
and the best way to get
rid of a negative seven x

00:01:03.317 --> 00:01:05.277
is to add seven x, so I'd wanna

00:01:05.277 --> 00:01:07.457
add seven x to the left hand side

00:01:07.457 --> 00:01:09.417
but in order to maintain this equality,

00:01:09.417 --> 00:01:11.117
I've gotta do it to both sides.

00:01:11.117 --> 00:01:14.677
So let's add seven x to both sides

00:01:14.677 --> 00:01:19.287
and then I'm going to be left with,

00:01:19.287 --> 00:01:21.987
on the left hand side,
negative seven x plus seven x,

00:01:21.987 --> 00:01:26.337
those cancel out, so
I get negative eight y

00:01:26.337 --> 00:01:30.567
is equal to seven x plus 28.

00:01:33.657 --> 00:01:35.617
And now, I just want a y out here,

00:01:35.617 --> 00:01:37.787
so I wanna get rid of this
negative eight coefficient

00:01:37.787 --> 00:01:38.717
and the best way to do that

00:01:38.717 --> 00:01:41.617
is divide both sides by negative eight.

00:01:41.617 --> 00:01:44.487
So divide both sides by negative eight

00:01:44.487 --> 00:01:46.887
and what are we left with?

00:01:46.887 --> 00:01:49.087
On the left hand side,
